The paper discusses the task of learning the structure of Bayesian Networks, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also compares different state-of-the-art methods for structural learning, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms, making cs.LG another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses statistical pitfalls within the algorithms, which could fall under the category of data mining (cs.DM) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses simulated data with different rates of noise, which could fall under the category of statistical inference (cs.SI).
